properties.areaDesc: San Juan County; Western Whatcom County; Western Skagit County
properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued January 11 at 2:46PM PST until January 13 at 12:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Heavy snow possible. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 6
inches possible.

* WHERE...San Juan County, Lowlands of western Whatcom County,
Lowlands of western Skagit County.

* WHEN...From Sunday afternoon through Sunday evening.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Gusty winds could
bring down tree branches.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Storm Watch means there is a potential for significant
snow, sleet, or ice accumulations that may impact travel. Continue
to monitor the latest forecasts.

Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SUNDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH SUNDAY EVENING
